crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The malware performs reconnaissance by enumerating running system services. It uses `OpenSCManagerA`, `OpenServiceA`, and `QueryServiceStatus` in a loop to check the status of a hardcoded list of services, a common technique to detect security products or sandbox environments. It ensures single-instance execution by using `FindWindowA` as a mutex. The main malicious logic is executed in a separate worker thread created via `CreateThread`. It also contains an anti-debugging check using `IsDebuggerPresent`.
